In the words of @daniabe, I’ve been reVAMPed! Allow me to reintroduce myself: I’m Countess Jen Lev, a member of Valiant Vampires’ Vampirc Council. As vampires, for hundreds of years we have been sucking blood from humans in an effort to find a cure for blood cancer. Under the leadership of Count Almogcula III, aka my good friend @almog.aa, we’re teaming up with @llsgreaterla & @llsusa to raise money to accelerate finding a cure for cancer while supporting and advocating for patients in need. 

The LLS “Dare to Dream” project aims to raise $175 million over the next 5 years to support global, collaborative research and treatments for children's blood cancers. Our team goal is to make a significant dent in that overall amount by raising over $102,510 *a vampire #* – and we need your help.

Please consider making a tax-deductible donation via the link in my bio. With enough vampires joining our efforts, we will finally be able to suck the cancer out of blood! 🩸

My best friend married the love of her life in the most magical wedding of all time and I didn’t shed a single tear… I torrentially downpoured many! It was a fantasy-filled extravaganza surrounded by elite company and copious amounts of joy, the perfect sendoff into her own “once upon a time” story. I said it in my speech, but there’s comfort to my family knowing that @embers247 is in my life, and there’s comfort to me knowing that Will is in hers. Love you both! ✨🏰❤️👑💍
